HEADWORD: Galangal
<hw>Ga*lan"gal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[OE. <ets>galingale</ets>, OF.
<ets>galingal</ets>, <ets>garingal</ets>, F. <ets>galanga</ets> (cf. Sp.
<ets>galanga</ets>), prob. fr. Ar. <ets>khalanj⟦amac⟧n</ets>. ]</ety>
<def>The pungent aromatic rhizome or tuber of certain East Indian or
Chinese species of <gen>Alpinia</gen> (<spn>Alpinia Galanga</spn> and
<spn>Alpinia officinarum</spn>) and of the <spn>K⟦ae⟧mpferia
Galanga</spn>), -- all of the Ginger family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

